|YKOAshad is an AshPunk desert continent west of the Darkwind mainland. Reach
the Oasis of Life across the Ocarian Sea, then follow its soot roads through
the Cinder Flats toward the continent's cities and hunting regions.

Severe and extreme Ashad heat ramps up while you remain exposed. Its first
check applies |YKBExposed|YKO. Continued checks refresh Exposed and apply
|RKBurning|YKO stacks. Daylight checks every 20 seconds at full strength;
dawn and twilight check every 25 seconds at reduced strength; night checks
every 30 seconds at half strength.

Marked shelters and rooms with light or no heat stop new exposure. Resist Heat
prevents the hazard. Ranger desert survival halves its Burning stacks,
Souvraeli adaptation reduces them further, and fire resistance mitigates the
damage Burning deals. Existing Burning decays normally after reaching safety;
Exposed expires shortly afterward.

Type |YKBheat|YKO in any Ashad room to see its tier, whether it protects you,
the current cadence, and the Burning stacks expected for your character.
